{"TopicId":139961,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"What if you could cut a photon in half?","CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-17T12:23:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-17T12:23:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://phys.org/news/2016-05-physicists.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://phys.org/news/2016-05-physicists.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing a specially constructed device they were able to measure the flow of angular momentum in a beam of light. They were also able, for the first time, to measure the variations in this flow caused by quantum effects. The experiments revealed a tiny shift, one-half of Planck\u0027s constant, in the angular momentum of each photon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WinkAllKerb\u0026#039;\u0026#039;","CreatedById":78047,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-17T12:24:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyour skin will change color ? :3 just KidDing for half or for part ; )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-17T12:24:59Z\u0022 title=\u002205/17/2016 12:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by WinkAllKerb\u0026#039;\u0026#039;\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-18T14:35:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmisleading title is misleading\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}